results.Name: Logon via forbidden logon method (Password)
results.Description: A successful or unsuccessful logon using a password logon method has occurred in a system where the password logon method is not allowed.Prerequisite: The necessary system settings must be applied in the systems. Enter these System IDs of these systems into the value list WhitelistSystemsPasswordLogonForbidden

results.Name: Logon of blacklisted users
results.Description: A logon by a blacklisted user has succeeded.Prerequisite: Only non-pseudonymized users can be added to the valuelist LogonBlacklistedUsers. A user is not pseudonymized in case its usertype corresponds to one of the usertypes defined in valuelist NonPseudonymizedUserTypes. Another option to avoid pseudonymization is to add usernames to the valuelist SAPStandardUsers. Then maintain the value list SuspiciousLogonBlacklistedUsers with the respective usernames.
